      "message": "Suggestion and see if this is better ?\n\n\n```\nFOR  ${line}  IN  @{lines}\n    ${line}\u003d  Strip String  ${line}\n    Continue For Loop If  \u0027${line}\u0027 \u003d\u003d \u0027\u0027\n    \n    ${should_filter}\u003d  Set Variable  ${False}\n    FOR  ${pattern}  IN  @{ignore_list}\n        IF  \u0027${pattern}\u0027 in \u0027${line}\u0027\n            ${should_filter}\u003d  Set Variable  ${True}\n            BREAK\n        END\n    END\n    \n    IF  not ${should_filter}\n        Append To List  ${filtered}  ${line}\n    END\nEND\n```\n\n\nSome improvement thoughs :\n1. Add BREAK to exit inner loop once pattern matches\n2. Skip empty lines early with Continue For Loop If\n3. Removed redundant final strip operation\n4. Better variable naming (${should_filter} vs ${skip})",
